The paper deals with temporal action localization, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses feature extraction methods and training strategies, which are related to machine learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the second most likely category. The paper also mentions fixed-size feature representation methods, which are related to multimedia. Therefore, cs.MM (Multimedia) is the third most likely category. The paper proposes a two-stage detector, which involves object detection, a subfield of artificial intelligence. Hence, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is the fourth most likely category. Finally, the paper discusses how each aspect influences the overall performance, which is related to information retrieval. Therefore, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is the fifth most likely category.
